like when l-- when l--

1008
01:14:34,599 --> 01:14:39,521
like when I step outside
of myself, you know?

1009
01:14:42,357 --> 01:14:44,359
And I see me...

1010
01:14:47,696 --> 01:14:50,657
I don't like what I see.

1011
01:14:50,699 --> 01:14:52,242
I really don't.

1012
01:14:52,325 --> 01:14:54,786
What's wrong with you?

1013
01:14:54,869 --> 01:14:58,832
Why don't you like yourself?

1014
01:14:58,873 --> 01:15:01,209
Sounds stupid, but...

1015
01:15:04,546 --> 01:15:06,589
because I'm failing shop.

1016
01:15:06,673 --> 01:15:09,551
We had this assignment,
you know...

1017
01:15:09,634 --> 01:15:12,220
to make this ceramic elephant.

1018
01:15:13,221 --> 01:15:14,514
And, um...

1019
01:15:14,556 --> 01:15:16,016
we're supposed to--

1020
01:15:16,057 --> 01:15:18,518
It was like a lamp.

1021
01:15:18,560 --> 01:15:23,064
When you pull the trunk,
the light goes on.

1022
01:15:24,524 --> 01:15:26,651
My light didn't go on.

1023
01:15:28,278 --> 01:15:31,281
I got an "F" on it.

1024
01:15:32,240 --> 01:15:34,534
I've never got an "F" in my life.

1025
01:15:34,993 --> 01:15:37,579
When I signed up for the course...

1026
01:15:37,662 --> 01:15:39,706
I thought I was playing it smart.

1027
01:15:39,789 --> 01:15:42,250
I thought, "I'll take shop.
lt'll be such an easy way...

1028
01:15:42,292 --> 01:15:44,294
to maintain
my grade point average."

1029
01:15:44,377 --> 01:15:47,380
Why'd you think it'd be easy?

1030
01:15:47,422 --> 01:15:50,884
Have you seen
some of the dopes that take shop?

1031
01:15:50,967 --> 01:15:54,929
I take shop.
You must be a fucking idiot.

1032
01:15:54,971 --> 01:15:56,765
Because I can't make a lamp?

1033
01:15:56,848 --> 01:15:59,434
No, you're a genius
because you can't make a lamp.

1034
01:16:00,935 --> 01:16:04,064
- What do you know about trigonometry?
- I could care less about it.

1035
01:16:04,105 --> 01:16:06,983
Without trigonometry,
there'd be no engineering.

1036
01:16:07,067 --> 01:16:10,737
- Without lamps, there'd be no light.
- So neither of you is better--

1037
01:16:10,779 --> 01:16:14,157
I can write with my toes.

1038
01:16:15,867 --> 01:16:18,661
I can also eat, brush my teeth--

1039
01:16:18,745 --> 01:16:22,499
- With your feet?
- Play the piano.

1040
01:16:22,582 --> 01:16:26,461
- I can make spaghetti.
- What can you do?

1041
01:16:28,129 --> 01:16:31,341
I can, uh,
tape all your buns together.

1042
01:16:31,424 --> 01:16:35,303
- I want to see what Claire can do.
- I can't do anything.

1043
01:16:35,387 --> 01:16:37,097
Everybody can do something.

1044
01:16:38,640 --> 01:16:41,184
There's one thing I can do.

1045
01:16:41,267 --> 01:16:43,353
Forget it.
It's way too embarrassing.

1046
01:16:43,436 --> 01:16:47,273
Ever seen "Wild Kingdom"?
He's been on for 30 years.

1047
01:16:48,441 --> 01:16:50,110
Okay.

1048
01:16:50,443 --> 01:16:52,904
You have to swear to God
you won't laugh.

1049
01:16:56,449 --> 01:16:58,118
Okay.

1050
01:17:00,161 --> 01:17:03,665
I can't believe
I'm actually doing this.

1051
01:17:18,179 --> 01:17:19,639
That's great!

1052
01:17:19,681 --> 01:17:22,684
Where'd you learn to do that?

1053
01:17:22,726 --> 01:17:24,519
Camp, seventh grade.

1054
01:17:30,358 --> 01:17:32,485
That was great, Claire.

1055
01:17:32,527 --> 01:17:35,822
My image of you
is totally blown.

1056
01:17:35,905 --> 01:17:38,575
You're a shit.
Don't do that to her.

1057
01:17:38,658 --> 01:17:41,327
- You swore to God you wouldn't laugh.
- Am I laughing?

1058
01:17:41,411 --> 01:17:44,039
You fucking prick!

1059
01:17:46,082 --> 01:17:48,752
What do you care what I think?

1060
01:17:50,045 --> 01:17:52,505
I don't even count, right?

1061
01:17:52,547 --> 01:17:56,259
I could disappear forever
and it wouldn't make any difference.

1062
01:17:58,261 --> 01:18:02,599
I may as well not even exist
at this school. Remember?

1063
01:18:06,019 --> 01:18:08,855
And, you,
don't like me anyway.

1064
01:18:08,897 --> 01:18:11,816
I have just as
many feelings as you do.

1065
01:18:11,900 --> 01:18:14,527
And it hurts just as much
when somebody steps on them.

1066
01:18:14,611 --> 01:18:16,529
God, you're so pathetic!

1067
01:18:16,571 --> 01:18:18,573
Don't you ever...

1068
01:18:18,656 --> 01:18:21,659
ever, compare yourself
to me, okay?

1069
01:18:21,743 --> 01:18:24,537
You got everything,
and I got shit.

1070
01:18:24,913 --> 01:18:26,873
Fucking Rapunzel, right?

1071
01:18:26,998 --> 01:18:30,210
School would probably shut down
if you didn't show up!

1072
01:18:30,251 --> 01:18:32,671
Queenie isn't here.

1073
01:18:33,004 --> 01:18:35,340
I like those earrings, Claire.

1074
01:18:35,423 --> 01:18:36,716
Shut up.

1075
01:18:36,800 --> 01:18:39,260
- Are those real diamonds, Claire?
- Just shut up.

1076
01:18:39,302 --> 01:18:41,304
I bet they are.

1077
01:18:41,346 --> 01:18:45,558
- Did you work for the money for those?
- Shut your mouth.

1078
01:18:45,767 --> 01:18:48,770
- Or did Daddy buy them for you?
- Shut up!

1079
01:18:48,853 --> 01:18:51,022
I bet he bought those.

1080
01:18:51,106 --> 01:18:54,859
I bet those were
a Christmas gift, right?

1081
01:18:54,943 --> 01:18:56,903
Know what I got for Christmas?

1082
01:18:56,986 --> 01:18:59,823
It was a banner-fucking-year
at the Bender family.

1083
01:18:59,906 --> 01:19:01,825
I got a carton of cigarettes.

1084
01:19:01,908 --> 01:19:04,077
The old man grabbed me and said,
"Smoke up, Johnny."

1085
01:19:04,119 --> 01:19:08,540
Go home and cry to your daddy.
Don't cry here, okay?

1086
01:19:21,386 --> 01:19:24,305
Will we be like our parents?

1087
01:19:24,389 --> 01:19:26,057
Not me...

1088
01:19:29,227 --> 01:19:30,562
ever.

1089
01:19:32,939 --> 01:19:34,274
It's unavoidable.

1090
01:19:35,817 --> 01:19:37,569
Just happens.

1091
01:19:37,652 --> 01:19:39,988
What happens?

1092
01:19:41,990 --> 01:19:44,951
When you grow up...

1093
01:19:44,993 --> 01:19:46,453
your heart dies.

1094
01:19:46,494 --> 01:19:47,787
Who cares?

1095
01:19:47,871 --> 01:19:50,957
I care.

1096
01:19:50,999 --> 01:19:55,628
I was just thinking,
I mean...

1097
01:19:55,670 --> 01:19:59,466
I know it's kind
of a weird time...

1098
01:19:59,507 --> 01:20:02,469
but I was just
wondering, um...

1099
01:20:02,510 --> 01:20:05,138
what will happen
on Monday?

1100
01:20:05,180 --> 01:20:07,474
When we're all together again.

1101
01:20:07,515 --> 01:20:10,518
I consider you guys my friends.

1102
01:20:13,021 --> 01:20:14,647
Am I wrong?

1103
01:20:16,024 --> 01:20:17,150
No.

1104
01:20:17,192 --> 01:20:20,779
So on Monday, what happens?

1105
01:20:20,862 --> 01:20:22,781
Still friends, you mean?

1106
01:20:22,864 --> 01:20:25,158
If we're friends now?

1107
01:20:25,200 --> 01:20:26,368
Yeah.

1108
01:20:27,369 --> 01:20:28,912
Want the truth?

1109
01:20:28,995 --> 01:20:31,373
Yeah, I want the truth.

1110
01:20:31,456 --> 01:20:33,833
I don't think so.

1111
01:20:35,543 --> 01:20:38,171
With all of us or just John?

1112
01:20:38,254 --> 01:20:41,216
With all of you.

1113
01:20:41,299 --> 01:20:45,220
- That's a real nice attitude, Claire.
- Oh, be honest, Andy.

1114
01:20:45,261 --> 01:20:48,181
If Brian came up to you on Monday,
what would you do?

1115
01:20:48,223 --> 01:20:52,644
Picture this.
You're there with all the sports.

1116
01:20:52,727 --> 01:20:55,563
You know exactly what you'd do.
You'd say hi and when he left...

1117
01:20:55,647 --> 01:20:59,192
you'd cut him up so your friends
wouldn't think you really liked him.

1118
01:20:59,818 --> 01:21:01,653
No way.

1119
01:21:01,736 --> 01:21:04,698
Okay. What if I came up to you?

1120
01:21:04,739 --> 01:21:08,118
- The same exact thing.
- You are a bitch!

1121
01:21:08,201 --> 01:21:12,038
Why? Because I'm telling
the truth, I'm a bitch?

1122
01:21:12,080 --> 01:21:14,874
No! 'Cause you know how shitty
that is to do to someone.

1123
01:21:14,916 --> 01:21:19,546
And you don't have the balls
to stand up to your friends.

1124
01:21:19,587 --> 01:21:21,715
What about you, you hypocrite?

1125
01:21:21,798 --> 01:21:25,218
Why don't you take Allison
to a heavy metal vomit party.

1126
01:21:25,260 --> 01:21:30,140
Take Brian or Andy out to
the parking lot to get high. Or me?

1127
01:21:30,223 --> 01:21:33,393
What would your friends say if we were
walking down the hall together?

1128
01:21:33,435 --> 01:21:35,437
They'd laugh their asses off.

1129
01:21:35,520 --> 01:21:38,231
You'd say we were doing it,
so they'd forgive you.

1130
01:21:38,273 --> 01:21:43,236
Don't talk about my friends! You don't
know them. You don't look at them.

1131
01:21:43,319 --> 01:21:46,322
And you certainly wouldn't
condescend to speak to them.

1132
01:21:46,406 --> 01:21:50,785
Just stick to what you know: shopping,
nail polish, your father's BMW...

1133
01:21:50,910 --> 01:21:54,039
- your drunk mother in the Caribbean--
- Shut up!

1134
01:21:54,122 --> 01:21:58,543
As far as being concerned about us
walking down the hallways together.

1135
01:21:58,626 --> 01:22:00,128
Forget it!
lt'll never happen!

1136
01:22:00,170 --> 01:22:03,506
Just bury your head
and wait for your fucking prom!

1137
01:22:03,590 --> 01:22:06,634
- I hate you!
- Yeah? Good!

1138
01:22:13,141 --> 01:22:15,935
I assume Allison and I are
better people than you guys?

1139
01:22:16,811 --> 01:22:18,772
Us weirdos?

1140
01:22:22,984 --> 01:22:26,279
- Would you do that to me?
- I don't have any friends.

1141
01:22:28,615 --> 01:22:31,910
- Well, if you did?
- No.

1142
01:22:34,162 --> 01:22:36,790
I don't think my kind
of friends would mind.

1143
01:22:37,916 --> 01:22:42,462
I just want to tell each of you
that I wouldn't do that.

1144
01:22:43,380 --> 01:22:45,965
I wouldn't and I will not.

1145
01:22:47,634 --> 01:22:49,636
Because I think that's real shitty.

1146
01:22:52,639 --> 01:22:55,183
Your friends wouldn't mind
because they look up to us.

1147
01:22:59,104 --> 01:23:01,648
You're so conceited, Claire.

1148
01:23:02,315 --> 01:23:04,317
You're so conceited.

1149
01:23:04,359 --> 01:23:06,653
You're so full of yourself. Why?

1150
01:23:07,237 --> 01:23:09,906
I'm not saying that
to be conceited.

1151
01:23:10,532 --> 01:23:13,868
I hate having to go along
with everything my friends say.

1152
01:23:13,952 --> 01:23:16,037
Then why do you do it?

1153
01:23:17,497 --> 01:23:19,499
I don't know. I don't--

1154
01:23:20,875 --> 01:23:22,961
You don't understand.
You don't--

1155
01:23:23,878 --> 01:23:27,215
You're not friends with the people
Andy and I are friends with.

1156
01:23:27,882 --> 01:23:32,012
You don't understand the pressure
they can put on you.

1157
01:23:32,721 --> 01:23:34,723
I don't understand what?

1158
01:23:34,806 --> 01:23:37,517
You think I don't
understand pressure?

1159
01:23:37,559 --> 01:23:39,102
Well, fuck you!

1160
01:23:39,185 --> 01:23:41,021
Fuck you!

1161
01:23:48,903 --> 01:23:52,365
You know why I'm here today?

1162
01:23:52,407 --> 01:23:54,034
Do you?

1163
01:23:58,246 --> 01:24:01,374
I'm here...because...

1164
01:24:01,416 --> 01:24:05,503
Mr. Ryan found
a gun in my locker.

1165
01:24:08,590 --> 01:24:13,053
- Why'd you have a gun?
- I tried.

1166
01:24:15,597 --> 01:24:18,892
You pull the fucking trunk...

1167
01:24:19,267 --> 01:24:21,102
and the light's supposed to go on.

1168
01:24:22,020 --> 01:24:24,064
It didn't go on.
I mean, l--

1169
01:24:26,274 --> 01:24:29,152
- What's the gun for?
- Just forget it.

1170
01:24:29,235 --> 01:24:31,404
You brought it up, man.

1171
01:24:33,448 --> 01:24:35,992
I can't have an "F".

1172
01:24:38,787 --> 01:24:40,747
I can't have it...

1173
01:24:42,207 --> 01:24:44,751
and I know
my parents can't have it.

1174
01:24:47,170 --> 01:24:49,255
Even if I ace
the rest of the semester...

1175
01:24:49,297 --> 01:24:53,259
I'm still only a "B."
Everything's ruined for me.

1176
01:24:53,802 --> 01:24:55,804
Brian.

1177
01:25:02,143 --> 01:25:04,604
Considering my options,
you know?

1178
01:25:04,729 --> 01:25:08,149
- Killing yourself is not an option.
- I didn't do it, did l!

1179
01:25:08,191 --> 01:25:10,026
No. I don't think so.

1180
01:25:10,110 --> 01:25:12,153
It was a handgun?

1181
01:25:14,739 --> 01:25:17,283
It was a flare gun.
Went off in my locker.

1182
01:25:17,617 --> 01:25:19,619
Really?

1183
01:25:21,621 --> 01:25:23,456
It's not funny.

1184
01:25:38,013 --> 01:25:39,973
Yes, it is.

1185
01:25:42,183 --> 01:25:44,686
Fucking elephant was destroyed.

1186
01:25:45,687 --> 01:25:49,357
Know what I did
to get in here?

1187
01:25:51,359 --> 01:25:52,902
Nothing.

1188
01:25:52,986 --> 01:25:56,573
I didn't have anything
better to do.

1189
01:26:02,203 --> 01:26:04,330
You're laughing at me.

1190
01:26:04,372 --> 01:26:05,623
No.

1191
01:26:05,707 --> 01:26:07,334
Yeah, you are.

1192
01:26:31,900 --> 01:26:34,486
# It seems so clear in black and white #

1193
01:26:34,569 --> 01:26:38,239
# The living color
tends to dull our sight #

1194
01:26:38,323 --> 01:26:41,659
# Like dynamite #

1195
01:26:41,743 --> 01:26:44,412
# Just imagine my surprise #

1196
01:26:44,496 --> 01:26:48,416
# When I looked into your eyes and saw #

1197
01:26:48,500 --> 01:26:50,502
# Through your disguise #

1198
01:26:51,836 --> 01:26:54,255
# If we dare expose our hearts #

1199
01:26:54,339 --> 01:26:56,758
# And just reveal the purest thoughts #

1200
01:26:56,841 --> 01:27:01,763
# And that is when
sensations start to grow #

1201
01:27:01,846 --> 01:27:04,099
# We are not alone #

1202
01:27:04,182 --> 01:27:06,601
# You find out
where you're coming from #

1203
01:27:06,685 --> 01:27:11,773
# There'll be somebody there
to break your fall #

1204
01:27:11,856 --> 01:27:14,109
# We are not alone #

1205
01:27:14,192 --> 01:27:16,444
# 'Cause when you
look out through the door #

1206
01:27:16,528 --> 01:27:20,865
# We're really not
the victims after all ##

1207
01:27:53,148 --> 01:27:54,607
Brian?

1208
01:27:54,649 --> 01:27:55,608
Hmm?

1209
01:27:55,650 --> 01:27:58,111
Are you going to write your paper?

1210
01:27:58,153 --> 01:27:59,654
Yeah. Why?

1211
01:28:01,656 --> 01:28:05,785
It's a waste for all of us
to write our paper.

1212
01:28:05,827 --> 01:28:08,038
Vernon wants us to.

1213
01:28:08,121 --> 01:28:12,375
True, but I think
we'd all kinda say the same thing.

1214
01:28:12,459 --> 01:28:17,047
You just don't want
to write your paper, right?

1215
01:28:17,130 --> 01:28:19,090
True, but...

1216
01:28:19,174 --> 01:28:20,967
you're the smartest, right?

1217
01:28:21,009 --> 01:28:22,844
Well...

1218
01:28:23,678 --> 01:28:26,348
We trust you.

1219
01:28:28,558 --> 01:28:30,393
Yeah.

1220
01:28:32,228 --> 01:28:34,230
All right.

1221
01:28:34,939 --> 01:28:36,941
I'll do it.

1222
01:28:37,233 --> 01:28:39,235
Great.

1223
01:28:51,206 --> 01:28:52,665
Come on.

1224
01:28:52,707 --> 01:28:54,834
Where are we going?

1225
01:28:54,876 --> 01:28:56,378
Come on.

1226
01:28:58,546 --> 01:29:00,507
[ Claire ] Don't be afraid.

1227
01:29:01,883 --> 01:29:04,094
Don't stick that in my eye.

1228
01:29:04,260 --> 01:29:07,263
I'm not sticking it. Just--
Go like that.

1229
01:29:09,516 --> 01:29:11,601
- [ Claire ] Good.
- [ Squealing ]

1230
01:29:14,145 --> 01:29:17,315
You look better without all that
black shit on your eyes.

1231
01:29:17,399 --> 01:29:19,901
Hey, I like that black shit.

1232
01:29:21,403 --> 01:29:23,363
This looks a lot better.

1233
01:29:23,613 --> 01:29:25,448
Look up.

1234
01:29:31,913 --> 01:29:34,874
[ Snorting ] Please.

1235
01:29:35,375 --> 01:29:38,003
Why are you being
so nice to me?

1236
01:29:38,086 --> 01:29:39,713
'Cause you're letting me.

1237
01:29:47,804 --> 01:29:49,889
